article.headline: UTEP 70, Portland State 57
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Fili Rivera scored 15 points and Chris Craig added 13 as Texas-El Paso beat Portland State 70-57 Saturday night. Roy Smallwood and John Tofi scored 11 points apiece for UTEP (3-0) while Omar Thomas added 10. Smallwood led the Miners with eight rebounds. Blake Walker led Portland State (1-2) with 24 points and 11 rebounds. Boxley Seamus added 15 points and seven rebounds. UTEP forced 23 turnovers while losing the ball just eight times and outscored Portland State 26-8 off turnovers. UTEP led 37-26 at halftime and never trailed in the second half.
